OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777327868
OL,3,CMPs to vote on whether PM should be
OL,4,Cinvestigated for misleading parliament
OL,6,FWords by ITV News Producer, Kieran
OL,7,FCarter
OL,9,FMPs will vote on whether to refer the
OL,10,Fprime minister to the privileges
OL,11,Fcommittee over claims he misled
OL,12,Fparliament about the appointment of
OL,13,FLord Peter Mandelson on at least two
OL,14,Fseparate occasions.
OL,16,FThis comes after the Speaker of the
OL,17,FHouse, Sir Lindsay Hoyle, on Monday
OL,18,Fgranted permission for the debate and
OL,19,Fvote to take place. Both are scheduled
OL,20,Ffor Tuesday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777327868
OL,3,CMPs to vote on whether PM should be
OL,4,Cinvestigated for misleading parliament
OL,6,FThe vote, pushed by numerous members
OL,7,Ffrom across the house as well as the
OL,8,Fleader of the opposition, has received
OL,9,Fcriticism from some Labour MPs,
OL,10,Fincluding Environment Secretary Emma
OL,11,FReynolds, who accused opposition
OL,12,Fparties of "playing silly political
OL,13,Fgames".
OL,15,FDame Emily Thornberry, Labour
OL,16,Fchairwoman of the Commons Foreign
OL,17,FAffairs Committee, told BBC Radio 4's
OL,18,FToday programme on Monday it was
OL,19,F"plain as the nose on my face" that
OL,20,Fthe move was timed to cause damage
OL,21,Fahead of the May elections.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777327868
OL,3,CMPs to vote on whether PM should be
OL,4,Cinvestigated for misleading parliament
OL,6,FShe did, however, add that an
OL,7,Finvestigation may be required "at some
OL,8,Fpoint in the future".
OL,10,FThe prime minister himself has denied
OL,11,Fhe misled the House, and stated his
OL,12,Fown fury at being kept in the dark by
OL,13,Fthe civil service.
OL,15,FShould the vote be successful, the
OL,16,Fcase will be referred to the
OL,17,FPrivileges Committee, where Sir Keir
OL,18,FStarmer could even be called to give
OL,19,Fevidence in person.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
